The error message "expected ',' or '...' before 'this'" typically occurs when there is a syntax error in the code. In this case, it seems like the issue is with the structure of the function declaration in C or C++.

The error is likely caused by the use of the keyword "this" as a parameter name in the function declaration. In C or C++, "this" is a reserved keyword and cannot be used as a parameter name in a function declaration.

To fix this error, you can simply rename the parameter "this" to a different name that is not a reserved keyword. For example, you can rename the parameter to "self":

```c
static void *get_data(struct graphics_priv *self, const char *type) {
    // function implementation
}
```

By changing the parameter name from "this" to something else, you should be able to resolve the error and successfully compile the code.

